{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Jk7ZxDxfemMvqdk6hRB1xs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can't patch the podManagementPolicy on an existing StatefulSet. I need to delete and recreate it. The PVCs should survive since they're not part of the StatefulSet spec itself.\n\nLet me delete the StatefulSet (keeping PVCs), recreate it with `Parallel` policy, then run `cockroach init`.\n\nActually, let me think about a different approach. Since I can't change the pod management policy after creation, I need to:\n1. Delete the StatefulSet (keeping PVCs since `--cascade=orphan`)\n2. Recreate it with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`\n3. Wait for all pods to be Running\n4. Run `cockroach init`\n\nAlternatively, I could relax the readiness probe to check the `/health` endpoint instead of `/health?ready=1`. The `/health` endpoint returns 200 once the node is up, even before initialization, while `/health?ready=1` returns 503 until the cluster is initialized. If I switch the readiness probe to use `/health`, pod-0 will become Ready as soon as it starts, allowing the other pods to begin starting in parallel.\n\nThe simplest approach is to delete the StatefulSet with `--cascade=orphan` to preserve the existing pods, then recreate it with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`. This way pod-0 gets adopted by the new StatefulSet, pods 1 and 2 are created, and then I can run `cockroach init`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":942,"cache_read_input_tokens":32505,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":942},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"72bce601-3a3f-4730-b16b-22d47db88613","uuid":"2b17fb26-abf8-4757-be5b-f34fe4b8247e","request_id":"req_011CccAchwis