imeline here is important - the original pod-0 started 11 minutes ago as a standalone instance, then the new StatefulSet took over and created pods 1 and 2. But I need to trace through whether pod-0 actually got restarted or if it's still the original instance running with the new cluster initialization. Pod-0 was the old pod while pods 1 and 2 were newly created, and when they started up they tried to join the cluster through the headless service DNS. The issue is that nodes 2 and 3 are showing NULL addresses in the node status, which suggests they may have briefly connected to the gossip network but their advertise addresses weren't resolvable. I need to dig into the container logs to understand what's happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":941,"cache_read_input_tokens":39210,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":941},"output_tokens":44,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"72bce601-3a3f-4730-b16b-22d47db88613","uuid":"87148be6-eeaf-465e-a16d-e7708c7d1332","request_id":"req_011CccB1T1Sa2oy3WasiB7n4"}
